memory:
  facts:
    - text: |
        FAFm is NOT about scoring. Memories are not scored. The .fafm spec (MEMORY-FORMAT.md)
        EXPLICITLY does not mandate measurement, drift detection, or refresh cycles. Per-fact
        fields like confidence_score and verification_status are PROVENANCE (witness data),
        not score components. Do not propose A/B/C/D/E score formulas for .fafm — that's a
        category error. .faf scores because completeness IS quality for project DNA; .fafm
        accumulates lived experience, which is not gradable the same way.
      id: "fafm-not-about-scoring"
      type: "feedback"
      priority: "critical"
      tags: ["doctrine", "format", "scoring", "wolfejam-2026-05-30"]
      source: "wolfejam direct correction 2026-05-30 + MEMORY-FORMAT.md spec confirmation"
      timestamp: "2026-05-30T17:37:31Z"
      confidence_score: 1.0
      verification_status: "verified"

    - text: |
