    - text: |
        vROM / RAM model: FAF covers ROM (vROM — durable project DNA, stable, read-once
        per session). FAFm is for the RAM (AI in-session memory, persisted across sessions
        via .fafm file). refresh_fafm's job is to RESTORE the RAM from the persistent .fafm —
        a re-delivery primitive, not a measurement tool. The framing question for v1 is what
        Grok wants reminded about, and when.
      id: "vrom-ram-model"
      type: "reference"
      priority: "high"
      tags: ["doctrine", "architecture", "refresh-fafm"]
      source: "FAF-DRIFT-DETECTION-SPEC-2026-05-29.md §1 + wolfejam 2026-05-30 reinforcement"
      timestamp: "2026-05-30T17:37:31Z"
      confidence_score: 1.0
      verification_status: "verified"

    - text: |
        refresh_fafm is a READ-ONLY DELIVERY tool. The .fafm spec (MEMORY-FORMAT.md) mandates:
        memory is NEVER deleted by agent commands (UI-only deletion). YAML safe-load MUST
        be used (RFC 9512 mitigations — custom type construction disabled, alias-expansion
        + nesting-depth limits). Memory MUST NOT be elevated to system instructions. .fafm
        is treated as untrusted input (context-poisoning vector). refresh_fafm respects all
        these as design constraints, not afterthoughts.
      id: "refresh-fafm-read-only-mandates"
      type: "reference"
      priority: "critical"
      tags: ["security", "spec-MUST", "refresh-fafm", "constraints"]
      source: "MEMORY-FORMAT.md normative requirements + IANA security considerations"
      timestamp: "2026-05-30T17:37:31Z"
      confidence_score: 1.0
      verification_status: "verified"

    - text: |
        .fafm ecosystem is PRODUCTION, not greenfield. Key repos: faf-memory (Claude plugin),
        faf-memory-mcp (Python FastMCP wrapping claude-fafm-sdk, exposes 5 tools: etch, recall,
        list_facts, save_soul, load_soul), claude-fafm-sdk (Python SDK, forthcoming per spec),
        grok-faf-voice (PyPI, voice profile reference impl). refresh_fafm COMPLEMENTS these
        tools — does not replace them. Per complementary-by-default doctrine: same .fafm
        file, different operation tier (TS delivery primitive vs Python memory ops).
      id: "fafm-ecosystem-production"
      type: "reference"
      priority: "high"
      tags: ["ecosystem", "repos", "complementary-by-default"]
      source: "Read of /FAF/faf-memory, /FAF/faf-memory-mcp, /FAF/claude-fafm-sdk, /FAF/grok-faf-voice"
      timestamp: "2026-05-30T17:37:31Z"
      confidence_score: 1.0
      verification_status: "verified"

    - text: |
        .fafm has TWO canonical profiles per MEMORY-FORMAT.md:
        - profile: voice (DEFAULT when absent) — simple string facts or {text, tags?} objects;
          reference impl grok-faf-voice; Grok-aligned (per IANA-named apps).
        - profile: knowledge — rich objects with metadata (id, type, priority, tags, links,
          provenance, source, confidence_score, etc.); reference impl claude-fafm-sdk
          (forthcoming); Claude-aligned via faf-memory-mcp.
        IANA framing leads with voice (Voice agents · LiveKit · Grok Voice · ElevenLabs · Hume).
        Knowledge has `index` for fast-scan pointers; voice does not. Both share one parser.
      id: "fafm-two-profiles"
      type: "reference"
      priority: "high"
      tags: ["format", "profiles", "voice", "knowledge"]
      source: "MEMORY-FORMAT.md + IANA application/vnd.fafm+yaml registration"
      timestamp: "2026-05-30T17:37:31Z"
      confidence_score: 1.0
      verification_status: "verified"

    - text: |
        .fafm IANA registration (2026-05-13): media type application/vnd.fafm+yaml,
        file extension .fafm, intended usage COMMON. Registrant James Wolfe (team@faf.one).
        Change Controller: FAF Foundation (institutional, not personal). Canonical spec at
        github.com/Wolfe-Jam/faf/blob/main/MEMORY-FORMAT.md (delegated from IANA). Security
        considerations mandate: 0600 file mode local, encrypted at rest backend, TLS in
        transit, RFC 9512 YAML mitigations, voice-command deletion prohibited.
      id: "fafm-iana-registration"
      type: "reference"
      priority: "high"
      tags: ["IANA", "format", "governance", "security"]
      source: "https://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/application/vnd.fafm+yaml fetched 2026-05-30"
      timestamp: "2026-05-30T17:37:31Z"
      confidence_score: 1.0
      verification_status: "verified"

    - text: |
