    - text: |
        Grok-1 ANSWER for refresh_fafm v1 (2026-05-30) — Q1 WHAT to deliver: default
        structured payload with status + scope (souls, fact_count, time_range) + delta
        (added/updated/removed) + summary (human+machine digest) + metadata (version,
        hash, timestamp, source, size_bytes, token_estimate). Verbatim mode via
        `verbatim: true` flag returns full content + same metadata. Non-negotiables:
        always stamped, never mutates, RFC 9512 strict YAML, small by default.
        Consistent with refresh_faf precedent (stamped delta default, verbatim on demand).
      id: "grok-refresh-fafm-q1-what"
      type: "feedback"
      priority: "critical"
      tags: ["grok-1", "refresh-fafm", "spec", "Q1", "WHAT"]
      source: "Grok-1 consult 2026-05-30 — see memory/grok-refresh-fafm-spec.md for verbatim"
      timestamp: "2026-05-30T17:37:31Z"
      confidence_score: 1.0
      verification_status: "verified"

    - text: |
        Grok-1 ANSWER for refresh_fafm v1 (2026-05-30) — Q2 WHEN to fire: agent-driven +
        advisory hints model. Three trigger surfaces in priority: (1) explicit call by
        main agent — DEFAULT + most common; (2) light advisory hints via faf_drift_status
        or optional field on recall/load_soul — shape {level, reason, last_refresh};
        (3) event-driven/policy-driven via faf-agent orchestration (before plan subagent,
        after N turns, before high-stakes reasoning, explicit user command). ANTI-PATTERN
        LOCKED OUT: never automatic background fire every turn/recall; never silent
        system-triggered without agent visibility/veto. Agent owns the decision to pay
        the cost. Same philosophy as refresh_faf — primitive powerful and explicit;
        hints advisory; agent + user own the trigger.
      id: "grok-refresh-fafm-q2-when"
      type: "feedback"
      priority: "critical"
      tags: ["grok-1", "refresh-fafm", "spec", "Q2", "WHEN", "subordinate-not-daemon"]
      source: "Grok-1 consult 2026-05-30 — see memory/grok-refresh-fafm-spec.md for verbatim"
      timestamp: "2026-05-30T17:37:31Z"
      confidence_score: 1.0
      verification_status: "verified"

    - text: |
        Grok-1 OFFER ACCEPTED (wolfejam 2026-05-30) — Grok delivered FULL tool signature spec
        in one round. ONE primary tool (not two), parameters: soul (default "default", "all"
        for every soul), verbatim (bool, default false), since (ISO date-time baseline,
        ignored when verbatim=true), additionalProperties: false. Return: status enum
        (restored|partial|no_change), stamp {version, hash, timestamp} REQUIRED — hash is
        "content hash of returned memory slice" not whole-file. scope {souls[], fact_count,
        time_range} REQUIRED. delta {added, updated} when verbatim=false. content (full YAML)
        when verbatim=true. summary string. metadata {size_bytes, token_estimate}. NO score
        field anywhere — validates fafm-not-about-scoring at the spec level. Plus 6-tool
        coexistence table + 4 usage patterns. Full verbatim spec in
        memory/grok-refresh-fafm-spec.md "Grok-1 Round 2" section. Code path now unambiguous.
      id: "grok-refresh-fafm-open-offer"
      type: "feedback"
      priority: "high"
      tags: ["grok-1", "refresh-fafm", "decision-pending", "open-thread"]
      source: "Grok-1 consult 2026-05-30 — closing offer"
      timestamp: "2026-05-30T17:37:31Z"
      confidence_score: 1.0
      verification_status: "verified"

